        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-29T12:37:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In my queries so far for Gold, I haven\u0027t found a need to store the trace id itself, and plan on making it from the keys as I pull them out. This might be due to the fact that Gold actually rarely (never) makes use of the trace id itself, but it might be something to consider.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 4,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "cb2ee826d544a57c30773468fee33f2c070b984e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1b2fea21_cb1748ea",
        "filename": "perf/migrations/cockroachdb/0002_create_initial_tables.up.sql",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 5,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-29T12:37:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "One reason I went with JSONB over STRING[] is that I don\u0027t have to sanitize the key/values. This may not matter much in practice, but with this array format, keys should not have equal signs, as that could throw off comparison.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 5,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 5,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "cb2ee826d544a57c30773468fee33f2c070b984e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9de7c7f0_f57541bc",
